1
00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:03,215
This series features fictional characters

2
00:00:03,215 --> 00:00:05,904
and content based on cases of depression.

3
00:00:05,904 --> 00:00:08,846
Real-life symptoms and behaviors

4
00:00:08,846 --> 00:00:11,800
may vary from person to person.

5
00:00:11,800 --> 00:00:16,148
For more info or psychiatric consultation,

6
00:00:16,148 --> 00:00:19,240
call your local area's mental health hotline.

7
00:00:19,240 --> 00:00:21,273
Those with depression or similar symptoms

8
00:00:21,273 --> 00:00:25,107
should watch with a close companion.

9
00:00:25,107 --> 00:00:28,333
I... caused trouble again, didn't I?

10
00:00:30,472 --> 00:00:35,055
I'm sorry for telling you I was fine.

11
00:00:35,055 --> 00:00:38,326
Pobmek, I need your help with something.

12
00:00:52,536 --> 00:00:53,708
I'm going to see my father.

13
00:00:53,708 --> 00:00:55,272
Come with me?

14
00:00:55,272 --> 00:00:59,211
No matter what happens,
I'll always be by your side.

15
00:01:02,008 --> 00:01:08,551
I heard that couples often get
to know each other better

16
00:01:08,551 --> 00:01:11,713
when they travel together.

17
00:01:11,713 --> 00:01:15,939
This is our first trip together.

18
00:01:19,265 --> 00:01:21,835
And it really is just like they say.

19
00:01:22,716 --> 00:01:24,839
Didn't I tell you to turn back there?

20
00:01:24,839 --> 00:01:26,362
See? Now we're lost.

21
00:01:26,362 --> 00:01:28,154
I've been holding the steering wheel
for six hours.

22
00:01:28,154 --> 00:01:30,218
My butt is getting all sore.

23
00:01:30,218 --> 00:01:33,926
I got foggy-headed and missed the turn!

24
00:01:41,512 --> 00:01:43,312
Thank you.

25
00:01:48,051 --> 00:01:49,182
Whoa.

26
00:01:49,182 --> 00:01:52,520
This is completely the wrong direction
from where we're headed.

27
00:01:52,520 --> 00:01:53,880
Look.

28
00:01:55,727 --> 00:01:57,436
I pinned the wrong location.

29
00:01:57,436 --> 00:01:58,856
See?

30
00:01:58,856 --> 00:02:00,241
I knew it.

31
00:02:00,241 --> 00:02:01,695
Yeah.

32
00:02:01,695 --> 00:02:02,942
It's my fault.

33
00:02:02,942 --> 00:02:04,922
I can't even drive.

34
00:02:05,761 --> 00:02:07,342
It's my fault.

35
00:02:07,342 --> 00:02:09,426
I can't even read a map right.

36
00:02:10,154 --> 00:02:11,912
Hey.

37
00:02:11,912 --> 00:02:14,448
That's not what I mean.

38
00:02:15,503 --> 00:02:18,413
Even though we've been together for so long,

39
00:02:18,413 --> 00:02:21,465
there are still things that surprise us.

40
00:02:21,465 --> 00:02:24,234
Solar is more sensitive than I thought.

41
00:02:24,234 --> 00:02:29,021
I guess I need to be more patient
and try to understand him better.

42
00:02:31,832 --> 00:02:33,299
Let's stay here tonight.

43
00:02:33,299 --> 00:02:35,550
We'll figure it out tomorrow.

44
00:02:46,077 --> 00:02:47,110
Solar!

45
00:02:47,110 --> 00:02:48,536
What's wrong?

46
00:02:48,536 --> 00:02:50,011
There!

47
00:02:50,011 --> 00:02:51,310
What?

48
00:02:51,310 --> 00:02:53,110
There!

49
00:03:01,629 --> 00:03:04,144
Shoo it away, Solar!

50
00:03:05,651 --> 00:03:06,995
Uncle.

51
00:03:09,226 --> 00:03:10,706
Sun?

52
00:03:12,600 --> 00:03:14,534
How did I end up here?

53
00:03:18,321 --> 00:03:20,102
You're not afraid of geckos, right?

54
00:03:20,102 --> 00:03:21,323
Go shoo it away for me.

55
00:03:21,323 --> 00:03:22,541
Go.

56
00:03:22,541 --> 00:03:24,341
Go, go, go.

57
00:04:25,425 --> 00:04:28,238
He switches to Sun
without falling asleep again?

58
00:04:28,238 --> 00:04:29,335
Yeah.

59
00:04:29,335 --> 00:04:31,425
I feel bad for Solar.

60
00:04:32,115 --> 00:04:33,642
For you too, man.

61
00:04:33,642 --> 00:04:34,714
Yeah.

62
00:04:34,714 --> 00:04:37,646
Did you guys find out anything else?

63
00:04:37,646 --> 00:04:38,710
Yeah.

64
00:04:38,710 --> 00:04:41,573
I checked the address on that old letter.

65
00:04:41,573 --> 00:04:44,608
Looks like it's really Mr. Sarun's address.

66
00:04:44,608 --> 00:04:48,424
But the bad news is
he already sold the house.

67
00:04:48,424 --> 00:04:50,962
Looks like he was having
some financial problems.

68
00:04:50,962 --> 00:04:52,906
But don't get discouraged yet.

69
00:04:52,906 --> 00:04:55,189
I have good news.

70
00:04:55,189 --> 00:04:57,366
I found his new place.

71
00:04:57,366 --> 00:04:59,554
It's a fruit orchard.

72
00:04:59,554 --> 00:05:02,260
Looks like he became a farmer.

73
00:05:02,260 --> 00:05:03,891
Wait.

74
00:05:04,579 --> 00:05:07,984
But he used to own a toy factory.

75
00:05:07,984 --> 00:05:10,090
How did he end up a farmer?

76
00:05:10,090 --> 00:05:12,017
We have no idea.

77
00:05:12,017 --> 00:05:14,898
You guys go check it out.
I'll send you the location.

78
00:05:15,823 --> 00:05:17,630
I just sent it.

79
00:05:18,720 --> 00:05:21,280
[Sarun's Plum Mango Orchard]

80
00:05:25,809 --> 00:05:28,314
You really can fix anything, Uncle Sarun.

81
00:05:28,314 --> 00:05:30,726
If you hadn't told me
you were a businessman from Bangkok,

82
00:05:30,726 --> 00:05:33,321
I'd think you're just one of the locals.

83
00:05:33,321 --> 00:05:36,427
Oh, I can't fix everything.

84
00:05:40,166 --> 00:05:42,834
You said
it keeps turning on and off by itself.

85
00:05:42,834 --> 00:05:44,469
The timer's broken.

86
00:05:44,469 --> 00:05:45,858
We'll have to buy a new one.

87
00:05:45,858 --> 00:05:48,820
I'll call and order one from Bangkok now.

88
00:05:49,514 --> 00:05:52,916
Sarun, some people from Bangkok
are here to see you.

89
00:05:52,916 --> 00:05:55,427
Delivery is fast these days, huh?

90
00:06:36,168 --> 00:06:37,330
Sir!

91
00:06:37,330 --> 00:06:39,081
Stop!

92
00:06:39,081 --> 00:06:40,881
Hey!

93
00:06:42,838 --> 00:06:44,938
Sir, stop!

94
00:06:44,938 --> 00:06:47,555
- Sir!
- Dad, stop!

95
00:06:57,337 --> 00:06:59,009
It's me.

96
00:06:59,009 --> 00:07:00,817
I'm your son, Sun.

97
00:07:07,539 --> 00:07:09,478
I'm sorry for running away earlier.

98
00:07:09,478 --> 00:07:11,662
I thought you were my creditors.

99
00:07:21,238 --> 00:07:23,515
Do you live here?

100
00:07:23,515 --> 00:07:25,472
How did you end up here?

101
00:07:25,472 --> 00:07:26,968
Well...

102
00:07:32,493 --> 00:07:33,905
Go away.

103
00:07:33,905 --> 00:07:34,930
Come on.

104
00:07:34,930 --> 00:07:37,634
Don't mind it.
It's been here for a long time.

105
00:07:47,460 --> 00:07:48,914
Uncle.

106
00:07:52,656 --> 00:07:54,024
Sun?

107
00:07:57,655 --> 00:07:59,600
Dad.

108
00:07:59,600 --> 00:08:01,960
- Dad!
- Hey.

109
00:08:06,919 --> 00:08:09,632
Dad, where's Mom?

110
00:08:11,309 --> 00:08:13,161
What did you say?

111
00:08:13,161 --> 00:08:15,346
I'm asking where Mom is.

112
00:08:16,739 --> 00:08:20,624
Well... I have something to tell you.

113
00:08:27,373 --> 00:08:30,263
It may sound a bit fantasy-like,

114
00:08:30,263 --> 00:08:33,876
but this is the reality we're facing.

115
00:08:44,930 --> 00:08:46,448
Sun.

116
00:08:49,914 --> 00:08:52,107
Is this really you, Sun?

117
00:08:52,107 --> 00:08:53,457
Yes.

118
00:08:54,430 --> 00:08:56,655
You want to see your mom, right?

119
00:08:56,655 --> 00:08:58,121
I do.

120
00:09:00,324 --> 00:09:03,924
Do you remember the last time you saw her?

121
00:09:09,133 --> 00:09:13,610
I remember she had just gotten off work.

122
00:09:15,640 --> 00:09:18,094
We were about to go home together,

123
00:09:18,094 --> 00:09:20,190
and she said this to me.

124
00:09:20,190 --> 00:09:25,128
Having you is the reason I lost everything!

125
00:09:27,858 --> 00:09:30,934
Is that all you remember?

126
00:09:31,626 --> 00:09:33,279
Do you remember anything else?

127
00:09:40,708 --> 00:09:42,646
What's wrong? Do you have a headache?

128
00:09:43,621 --> 00:09:45,526
I'll get you some medicine.

129
00:09:45,526 --> 00:09:47,037
I'll be right back.

130
00:09:52,718 --> 00:09:54,459
How are you feeling?

131
00:09:55,303 --> 00:09:57,211
Are you okay?

132
00:09:57,211 --> 00:10:00,743
I feel kind of uneasy.

133
00:10:07,639 --> 00:10:09,013
Sir!

134
00:10:10,068 --> 00:10:12,124
- What are you doing?
- Running away, obviously!

135
00:10:12,124 --> 00:10:13,505
- Running away?
- Yeah!

136
00:10:13,505 --> 00:10:15,333
- Running away from what?
- Dad!

137
00:10:15,333 --> 00:10:16,787
What are you doing?

138
00:10:17,675 --> 00:10:19,344
You want me to take responsibility, right?

139
00:10:19,344 --> 00:10:21,738
I'm too poor to be responsible for you.

140
00:10:21,738 --> 00:10:23,148
Hey!

141
00:10:23,148 --> 00:10:24,568
Ouch!

142
00:10:25,388 --> 00:10:28,436
Sun! Are you okay? Are you hurt?

143
00:10:30,306 --> 00:10:34,933
I'm not hurt, but my dad sure will be.

144
00:10:34,933 --> 00:10:36,513
Solar?

145
00:10:37,345 --> 00:10:38,927
Solar!

146
00:10:41,083 --> 00:10:44,343
He's really fit for his age.

147
00:10:50,841 --> 00:10:52,412
Dad!

148
00:11:01,946 --> 00:11:04,076
How much longer are you going to
keep running from me?

149
00:11:26,312 --> 00:11:28,714
I still don't even know

150
00:11:30,874 --> 00:11:33,041
what I'm going to say to you, Dad.

151
00:11:35,292 --> 00:11:37,693
I just don't want to run away
from my problems anymore.

152
00:11:42,847 --> 00:11:47,043
This is the letter
you sent to Teacher Pranee.

153
00:11:50,633 --> 00:11:52,335
I already read it,

154
00:11:53,210 --> 00:11:57,755
and I understand why you left me.

155
00:12:00,256 --> 00:12:02,534
I just...

156
00:12:02,534 --> 00:12:04,523
wanted to come and apologize.

157
00:12:07,352 --> 00:12:13,843
I'm sorry for being the reason
Mom made that decision.

158
00:12:23,015 --> 00:12:24,438
Let's go.

159
00:12:29,954 --> 00:12:31,748
Wait, don't go yet.

160
00:12:36,703 --> 00:12:38,636
Can you come with me, Sun?

161
00:12:56,049 --> 00:13:01,021
These are some of your mom's things
that I kept.

162
00:13:02,223 --> 00:13:06,668
I was saving them for you, Sun,

163
00:13:06,668 --> 00:13:10,442
just in case we ever saw each other again.

164
00:13:20,945 --> 00:13:23,433
Is this all you're giving me?

165
00:13:23,433 --> 00:13:24,722
I'm leaving.

166
00:13:25,534 --> 00:13:26,800
Sun.

167
00:13:30,568 --> 00:13:33,818
You think you're the reason Mom did that,

168
00:13:34,851 --> 00:13:36,425
but I don't agree.

169
00:13:39,130 --> 00:13:44,841
Okay, I know I have no right
to change the way you think,

170
00:13:46,297 --> 00:13:50,624
but I can assure you
that you're not the reason.

171
00:13:54,954 --> 00:14:01,101
If you came here to ask
why your mom decided to do that,

172
00:14:04,518 --> 00:14:06,335
it's because of me.

173
00:14:13,943 --> 00:14:20,515
Solar, which animal do you think
needs special care?

174
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:23,268
A baby bird.

175
00:14:23,268 --> 00:14:25,201
Why do you think so?

176
00:14:25,201 --> 00:14:28,397
Because it can't fly on its own yet.

177
00:14:28,397 --> 00:14:32,054
And what about a lion cub like you, Solar?

178
00:14:32,054 --> 00:14:35,148
Do you need special care too?

179
00:14:35,895 --> 00:14:38,520
I know it's all about video games these days,

180
00:14:38,520 --> 00:14:41,389
but toys are tangible.

181
00:14:41,389 --> 00:14:43,869
They're still in demand.

182
00:14:45,718 --> 00:14:48,358
How about you let me know
your decision later?

183
00:14:48,358 --> 00:14:49,960
Alright, bye.

184
00:15:01,332 --> 00:15:02,345
Teacher Pranee.

185
00:15:02,345 --> 00:15:04,264
Sir! Come here.

186
00:15:04,264 --> 00:15:07,451
I think I hear people
arguing inside the house.

187
00:15:07,451 --> 00:15:10,083
- Inside the house?
- Yeah, for a while now.

188
00:15:11,541 --> 00:15:13,840
- Thank you.
- No problem.

189
00:15:14,860 --> 00:15:16,159
Answer me.

190
00:15:16,159 --> 00:15:18,625
Why couldn't you hold onto it?

191
00:15:19,434 --> 00:15:21,277
- Huh?
- Hey.

192
00:15:23,746 --> 00:15:25,847
What happened?

193
00:15:25,847 --> 00:15:27,747
See for yourself.

194
00:15:32,606 --> 00:15:34,684
Sun,

195
00:15:34,684 --> 00:15:36,750
do you want to sit down and play?

196
00:15:36,750 --> 00:15:39,426
Come on, it's okay.

197
00:15:45,265 --> 00:15:47,625
Do you want to sit down and rest?

198
00:15:47,625 --> 00:15:49,945
I'll clean this up.

199
00:16:11,957 --> 00:16:14,557
After your mom went on maternity leave,

200
00:16:14,557 --> 00:16:17,037
her show got cancelled.

201
00:16:18,210 --> 00:16:20,977
She probably wanted to feel seen again.

202
00:16:20,977 --> 00:16:23,390
Come on. Waist twists!

203
00:16:23,390 --> 00:16:25,302
Arm circles!

204
00:16:25,302 --> 00:16:29,933
But that chance kept slipping further away.

205
00:16:32,360 --> 00:16:37,076
Another person I felt just as much for
was you, Sun.

206
00:16:39,320 --> 00:16:41,367
I'm fine.
[Enjoy eating, my hero]

207
00:16:41,367 --> 00:16:45,483
I have fangs to protect myself.

208
00:16:45,483 --> 00:16:50,900
Oh, you're the best, Little Solar.

209
00:16:50,900 --> 00:16:57,600
Solar is fine because
he has fangs to protect himself.

210
00:16:57,600 --> 00:16:59,207
Yay!

211
00:17:05,132 --> 00:17:10,504
I did everything I could to get your mom
a chance to talk to the station.

212
00:17:10,504 --> 00:17:13,686
I hoped she could get her show back,

213
00:17:13,686 --> 00:17:17,290
and feel proud of herself again.

214
00:17:17,290 --> 00:17:18,416
Okay.

215
00:17:18,416 --> 00:17:20,993
So our family could be happy again.

216
00:17:20,993 --> 00:17:22,528
Are you happy for your mom? She got a job.

217
00:17:22,528 --> 00:17:26,946
But things didn't turn out the way I hoped.

218
00:17:27,678 --> 00:17:32,083
I still admire your show,
and everyone else does too.

219
00:17:32,083 --> 00:17:37,744
But after you went on leave,
things are different now.

220
00:17:37,744 --> 00:17:42,450
Times have changed, okay?

221
00:17:44,988 --> 00:17:46,660
It's okay.

222
00:17:48,413 --> 00:17:51,188
Let's come up with some new ideas
to pitch to them.

223
00:17:51,188 --> 00:17:54,250
You've done it before.
I'm sure you can do it again.

224
00:17:55,402 --> 00:17:56,561
Right, Sun?

225
00:17:56,561 --> 00:17:58,878
Yes, you can do it, Mom.

226
00:17:58,878 --> 00:18:00,191
Okay?

227
00:18:04,197 --> 00:18:06,323
Let me take this call.

228
00:18:07,623 --> 00:18:08,912
Hello?

229
00:18:14,540 --> 00:18:15,876
Got it.

230
00:18:58,709 --> 00:19:00,407
Actually,

231
00:19:01,229 --> 00:19:03,536
I was there that day,

232
00:19:04,275 --> 00:19:06,016
but I can only remember bits and pieces.

233
00:19:07,361 --> 00:19:10,053
It must've been painful for Sun.

234
00:19:13,202 --> 00:19:16,219
But for me,

235
00:19:17,193 --> 00:19:19,081
that pain didn't end that day.

236
00:19:33,067 --> 00:19:35,245
After that incident,

237
00:19:38,099 --> 00:19:40,736
Sun didn't regain consciousness.

238
00:19:42,615 --> 00:19:46,844
Even though the doctor said
Sun was out of danger,

239
00:19:46,844 --> 00:19:50,884
they didn't know when he would wake up.

240
00:19:50,884 --> 00:19:53,230
Leroy proudly marched into the forest.

241
00:19:53,230 --> 00:19:56,477
Teacher Pranee was so worried about Sun,

242
00:19:56,477 --> 00:19:58,841
and came to visit him often.

243
00:20:01,652 --> 00:20:05,191
And then, a miracle happened.

244
00:20:05,191 --> 00:20:07,396
Who's Sun?

245
00:20:07,396 --> 00:20:09,435
My name's not Sun.

246
00:20:10,927 --> 00:20:13,454
I'm Solar.

247
00:20:13,454 --> 00:20:16,155
Solar means bright sunshine,

248
00:20:16,155 --> 00:20:19,901
ready to heal everyone's heart.

249
00:20:19,901 --> 00:20:22,222
You don't remember anything?

250
00:20:22,222 --> 00:20:24,908
Who are you, Auntie?

251
00:20:24,908 --> 00:20:27,331
Are you my mom?

252
00:20:55,497 --> 00:20:57,977
I'm sorry I left you...

253
00:20:59,409 --> 00:21:01,432
without telling anyone, Sun.

254
00:21:04,383 --> 00:21:09,531
All I left you was that first letter,

255
00:21:10,558 --> 00:21:13,430
and the money from selling my company.

256
00:21:15,051 --> 00:21:18,484
Actually, I wrote many more letters, but...

257
00:21:19,632 --> 00:21:21,615
I was too afraid to send them.

258
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:27,760
Because every time I thought about that day,

259
00:21:27,760 --> 00:21:30,760
when you woke up as someone else,

260
00:21:32,695 --> 00:21:40,128
it reminded me that my son wanted to escape.

261
00:21:44,444 --> 00:21:47,895
Who would want
to be with a terrible father like me?

262
00:22:05,496 --> 00:22:07,590
It's actually me...

263
00:22:07,590 --> 00:22:11,023
who was the reason
your mom decided to do that.

264
00:22:35,327 --> 00:22:37,853
It's not your fault...

265
00:22:40,037 --> 00:22:42,350
Mom made that decision.

266
00:22:45,197 --> 00:22:47,931
It's not your fault either, Sun.

267
00:23:07,443 --> 00:23:08,858
Solar,

268
00:23:11,418 --> 00:23:12,959
look behind the photo.

269
00:23:17,918 --> 00:23:19,547
What's this key?

270
00:23:19,547 --> 00:23:21,676
It's the key to the toy box.

271
00:23:22,739 --> 00:23:25,720
But I don't know why your mom put it there.

272
00:24:00,909 --> 00:24:06,843
These past few years
have been the worst of my life.

273
00:24:12,890 --> 00:24:17,441
I don't understand
what's really going on with me.

274
00:24:19,032 --> 00:24:21,911
I feel like...

275
00:24:21,911 --> 00:24:24,130
I'm worthless.

276
00:24:25,924 --> 00:24:33,904
It's gotten so bad
that I don't even know who I am anymore.

277
00:24:35,290 --> 00:24:40,744
It feels like I'm not myself anymore.

278
00:24:42,202 --> 00:24:45,643
Even though I've been trying
to be myself again,

279
00:24:47,006 --> 00:24:49,725
it's just too hard.

280
00:24:50,940 --> 00:24:53,522
I'm so exhausted.

281
00:24:54,263 --> 00:24:57,316
I can barely take it anymore.

282
00:24:57,316 --> 00:25:00,130
Mom, you're going back to work, right?

283
00:25:06,241 --> 00:25:08,081
Probably not.

284
00:25:09,305 --> 00:25:14,700
Having you is the reason I lost everything!

285
00:25:34,205 --> 00:25:38,306
Sun, I'm sorry.

286
00:25:40,300 --> 00:25:43,228
I didn't mean that.

287
00:25:54,684 --> 00:25:57,086
Little Sun,

288
00:25:57,086 --> 00:26:02,947
your mom asked me to tell you she's sorry.

289
00:26:02,947 --> 00:26:05,747
She didn't mean what she said.

290
00:26:07,857 --> 00:26:12,855
From now on,
she'll be more careful with her words.

291
00:26:16,000 --> 00:26:18,114
Please don't be mad at her.

292
00:26:30,460 --> 00:26:38,926
But I know how much I matter
to both your dad and you.

293
00:26:45,835 --> 00:26:49,112
You two are the only thing

294
00:26:49,112 --> 00:26:54,120
that makes me want to keep living.

295
00:26:59,102 --> 00:27:02,456
I love your dad,

296
00:27:03,218 --> 00:27:06,018
and I love you so much, Sun.

297
00:27:08,169 --> 00:27:11,769
But the person I forgot to love the most...

298
00:27:15,653 --> 00:27:17,280
was...

299
00:27:19,585 --> 00:27:21,455
myself.

300
00:27:49,474 --> 00:27:53,536
Please don't cry, my hero.

301
00:28:01,351 --> 00:28:02,965
Sun,

302
00:28:04,303 --> 00:28:06,045
is this really you?

303
00:28:08,116 --> 00:28:10,774
I remember everything now, Dad.

304
00:28:12,606 --> 00:28:15,551
Mom didn't want to leave us.

305
00:28:16,530 --> 00:28:18,941
She did that to protect me.

306
00:28:23,672 --> 00:28:27,993
I know you've done everything...

307
00:28:29,513 --> 00:28:34,185
to take care of me, and to take care of Mom.

308
00:28:37,018 --> 00:28:38,730
I know it,

309
00:28:40,213 --> 00:28:42,813
and Mom always knew it too.

310
00:28:44,800 --> 00:28:46,343
So,

311
00:28:48,906 --> 00:28:51,398
let's live happily...

312
00:28:53,137 --> 00:28:55,326
for her.

313
00:29:02,263 --> 00:29:03,824
Okay.

314
00:30:31,479 --> 00:30:33,346
Sun is going to be asleep for a while, huh?

315
00:30:33,346 --> 00:30:34,862
Yes.

316
00:30:39,180 --> 00:30:41,292
Alright. Here.

317
00:30:42,180 --> 00:30:43,927
These are plum mangoes from my orchard.

318
00:30:43,927 --> 00:30:47,099
Take them all and share them
with your friends in Bangkok.

319
00:30:47,099 --> 00:30:48,613
Thank you so much.

320
00:30:48,613 --> 00:30:51,227
But I didn't prepare anything for you.

321
00:30:51,227 --> 00:30:52,666
Oh, don't worry.

322
00:30:52,666 --> 00:30:57,533
Taking care of Sun and Solar
is already more than enough.

323
00:30:57,533 --> 00:30:59,012
Thank you.

324
00:31:01,719 --> 00:31:06,393
It's Solar who's been taking care of me.

325
00:31:06,393 --> 00:31:08,566
Without him,

326
00:31:08,566 --> 00:31:11,653
I don't know what my life would be right now.

327
00:31:15,367 --> 00:31:17,107
Wait.

328
00:31:17,107 --> 00:31:18,627
Here.

329
00:31:21,673 --> 00:31:24,086
- What's this letter?
- It's not a letter.

330
00:31:24,086 --> 00:31:26,446
It's a list of places to visit.

331
00:31:26,446 --> 00:31:28,546
There are a lot of great spots on it.

332
00:31:28,546 --> 00:31:29,893
Thank you so much.

333
00:31:29,893 --> 00:31:31,670
Enjoy your trip.

334
00:31:33,879 --> 00:31:35,342
Sir,

335
00:31:37,040 --> 00:31:40,946
whenever it's convenient for you,

336
00:31:40,946 --> 00:31:44,240
please come visit us in Bangkok sometime.

337
00:31:46,900 --> 00:31:48,280
Okay.

338
00:32:19,820 --> 00:32:21,920
What are you doing hiding here?

339
00:32:25,779 --> 00:32:27,913
Just getting some air.

340
00:32:30,380 --> 00:32:31,757
Hey.

341
00:32:32,840 --> 00:32:34,746
Do you think it's weird?

342
00:32:36,813 --> 00:32:38,405
Weird?

343
00:32:39,173 --> 00:32:41,119
What's weird?

344
00:32:41,119 --> 00:32:44,073
I'm not as good at this as I used to be.

345
00:32:44,073 --> 00:32:47,933
It's not like when Little Sun does it.

346
00:32:49,140 --> 00:32:53,266
It's probably because you're you,

347
00:32:54,607 --> 00:32:56,840
and Sun is Sun.

348
00:33:06,973 --> 00:33:11,473
I think Little Sun understands now

349
00:33:12,147 --> 00:33:15,046
that he shouldn't have suppressed his pain,

350
00:33:15,719 --> 00:33:20,206
and created me to forget his painful past.

351
00:33:21,166 --> 00:33:23,746
When Sun remembered everything,

352
00:33:24,553 --> 00:33:27,420
and accepted all that happened,

353
00:33:29,999 --> 00:33:31,958
I could feel that...

354
00:33:33,315 --> 00:33:35,386
he'd finally let it go.

355
00:33:39,860 --> 00:33:43,526
He's healed now.

356
00:33:45,999 --> 00:33:52,833
If Sun is healed,
and you're the identity he created,

357
00:33:54,513 --> 00:33:56,737
then why haven't you gone back to being Sun?

358
00:33:58,700 --> 00:34:00,596
Where did he go?

359
00:34:11,660 --> 00:34:16,160
It seems like Little Sun has gone back
into my heart,

360
00:34:16,160 --> 00:34:18,161
and fallen into a very deep sleep.

361
00:34:19,366 --> 00:34:24,433
It's like he chose
to let me live my life from now on.

362
00:34:25,506 --> 00:34:28,419
Why would Sun do that?

363
00:34:29,966 --> 00:34:32,433
I think he wants us to be together.

364
00:34:37,926 --> 00:34:40,040
You're saying...

365
00:34:40,833 --> 00:34:42,672
Little Sun and I

366
00:34:44,039 --> 00:34:46,626
don't have to switch every other day anymore.

367
00:34:48,366 --> 00:34:52,633
Sun wants me to be with you every day.

368
00:35:03,446 --> 00:35:07,240
That kid always knows too much.

369
00:35:10,860 --> 00:35:12,520
Before we split up for work today...

370
00:35:12,520 --> 00:35:15,192
After everything was resolved,

371
00:35:15,192 --> 00:35:19,226
- Hi.
- Solar looks happier.

372
00:35:20,973 --> 00:35:24,546
- Nothing's weighing on his mind anymore.
- What?

373
00:35:29,491 --> 00:35:31,022
I think it's working now, Dad.

374
00:35:32,426 --> 00:35:33,527
Oh!

375
00:35:33,527 --> 00:35:35,333
Hey!

376
00:35:35,333 --> 00:35:37,133
Yay!

377
00:35:37,133 --> 00:35:40,567
And it's probably not just Solar
who has changed.

378
00:35:40,567 --> 00:35:41,913
You're pretty good.

379
00:35:41,913 --> 00:35:43,507
- Thank you so much, Dad.
- How do you know how to fix this?

380
00:35:43,507 --> 00:35:44,980
Excuse me.

381
00:35:44,980 --> 00:35:46,347
Is there anything I can help with?

382
00:35:46,347 --> 00:35:51,240
Do you usually sweep before you mop,
or mop before you sweep?

383
00:35:55,727 --> 00:35:59,946
But some things never change.

384
00:36:36,687 --> 00:36:39,440
- Bye-bye, Dad.
- Bye-bye.

385
00:36:43,680 --> 00:36:45,960
[The seller's asleep!
Please pay via PromptPay]

386
00:37:21,499 --> 00:37:23,513
Solar! What's wrong?

387
00:37:23,513 --> 00:37:25,007
There!

388
00:37:37,833 --> 00:37:39,054
Hold on.

389
00:37:39,867 --> 00:37:41,893
You're not even taking a shower.

390
00:37:41,893 --> 00:37:43,687
Why did you come in here?

391
00:37:48,927 --> 00:37:55,820
Actually, I snuck in to write you a postcard.

392
00:37:57,699 --> 00:37:59,738
I was about to write you one too.

393
00:38:05,586 --> 00:38:07,926
What were you going to write?

394
00:38:08,579 --> 00:38:09,982
Well,

395
00:38:10,993 --> 00:38:12,740
I was going to compliment you

396
00:38:14,100 --> 00:38:17,126
on how you managed to let go of your trauma.

397
00:38:18,113 --> 00:38:19,857
That's all.

398
00:38:21,320 --> 00:38:23,740
What about you?
What were you going to write to me?

399
00:38:26,446 --> 00:38:29,046
I just wanted to write

400
00:38:30,800 --> 00:38:34,240
that no matter how much we've been through,

401
00:38:34,873 --> 00:38:39,820
there will always be new things for us
to learn about each other

402
00:38:40,473 --> 00:38:42,786
and for me to get to know you better.

403
00:38:45,213 --> 00:38:47,153
Without you,

404
00:38:48,613 --> 00:38:52,166
I don't know how I'd live.

405
00:38:56,846 --> 00:38:58,589
Thank you so much.

406
00:39:02,387 --> 00:39:04,333
Thank you so much, too.

407
00:39:10,919 --> 00:39:13,433
Go. I'm going to take a shower.

408
00:39:16,127 --> 00:39:18,866
You're going to trick me
into thinking you're showering again.

409
00:39:18,866 --> 00:39:22,334
This time, I'm standing guard.

410
00:39:24,327 --> 00:39:26,498
Look who's playing the discipline teacher.

411
00:39:28,333 --> 00:39:30,100
Okay.

412
00:39:30,100 --> 00:39:32,455
Just make sure standing guard is all you do.

413
00:40:05,800 --> 00:40:08,003
I thought you said
you were just going to stand guard.

414
00:40:08,767 --> 00:40:10,347
I changed my mind.

415
00:40:16,333 --> 00:40:19,866
And it's probably just like Solar said.

416
00:40:21,566 --> 00:40:24,820
We'll always have new things

417
00:40:24,820 --> 00:40:29,053
to learn and get to know each other better.

418
00:40:30,413 --> 00:40:32,973
As long as we don't run away from them

419
00:40:32,973 --> 00:40:35,653
and keep holding each other's hands,

420
00:40:35,653 --> 00:40:37,413
that's enough.

421
00:41:16,140 --> 00:41:20,493
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

422
00:41:23,153 --> 00:41:26,487
If Sun came to the beach,

423
00:41:26,487 --> 00:41:28,376
what do you think he'd do first?

424
00:41:29,247 --> 00:41:30,540
Thank you so much

425
00:41:30,540 --> 00:41:33,600
for bringing Sun and me
to the beach like you promised.

426
00:41:33,600 --> 00:41:37,240
I want to play in the water
with both you and Sun, I guess.

427
00:41:37,240 --> 00:41:40,113
Hey. Solar.

428
00:41:40,113 --> 00:41:43,513
Teacher Solar is about to propose
to Teacher Pobmek!

429
00:41:43,513 --> 00:41:45,313
Do it!
